{"type": "article", "id": 32764, "title": "这 10 个 Instagram 账号，每一个都在做当代艺术展", "description": "日常物件在重复一万遍的影像中闪闪发光。", "date": "2016-10-07T23:03:06Z", "super_tag": "", "tags": [{"id": 26, "name": "instagram"}, {"id": 9783, "name": "美"}, {"id": 33304, "name": "连线杂志"}], "category": 17, "author": 619958, "comment_count": 4, "praise_count": 566, "image": "img/article/article_show/2016092902005728gcmNiIDOVBRfCr.png", "contents": "<p>这周，<a href=\"https://www.wired.com/2016/09/10-hyper-specific-instagram-accounts-thrill-inner-design-nerd/\" rel=\"nofollow\">《连线》杂志选出了 10 个设计类 Instagram 账号</a>，号称能够“唤起内心对设计的痴迷”。滤镜让普通人很容易能上传还过得去的照片，但要与众不同，主题很关键。一些 Instagram 账号一丝不苟地记录一个主题的东西——既可以是自然景观的壮丽航拍，也可以仅仅是各种各样的烘手机。</p><p>这些 Instagram 账号的操作者，与其说是用户，不如说是线上展览的策展人。</p><p>以下是 10 个推荐账号，点击标题可直接进入 Instagram 页面。</p><p class=\"\"><b><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/docubyte/\" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"\">1. James Ball (@docubyte)</a></b></p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201609290131122zxh8nogUtksAj4M.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.166407\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160929013131WRIl3STDCB6pxgUP.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.857143\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201609290131440owbmXSPTiEp6dyu.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.166407\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160929013203DA1YySl3Rax9wLJf.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.857143\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160929013219QspHZxr7KwFXnYjv.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.857143\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><p class=\"\">在不是很久的以前，“计算机”还不是一件轻薄、时尚、能够放进你口袋的电子产品，而是巨大、壮观、闪烁着指示灯的机器。艺术家 James Ball 在他的 @docubyte 账号中，<a href=\"http://www.docubyte.co.uk/projects/guide-to-computing/#.V-vsOIT4PbR\" rel=\"nofollow\">展出了一系列纪念往日的“电脑指南”照片</a>，10 个从 1940 年代到 70 年代的计算机在纯色背景下展示外露的电线、繁多的按钮和厚厚的显示屏。这些计算机大部分来自伦敦科学博物馆（Science Museum in London），英国布莱切利园（Bletchley Park）国家电脑博物馆（National Museum of Computing）——图灵曾经在此工作过。</p><p><b><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/matchbookdiaries/\" rel=\"nofollow\">2. Matchbook Diaries (@matchbookdiaries)</a></b></p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160929012343obN0ZQxuMj9SYVhm.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.972973\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160929012410zvskJUFQ2KG3ujwr.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.998012\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><br></div><p class=\"\"></p><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201609290124266VihUpFGBZtDXegS.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.852652\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure><p></p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160929012447d5GjX2mlNUpTZ0FM.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.842000\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160929012711JCBd9auxOPAVfS6h.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.766304\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure></div><p>餐馆制作精美的火柴盒可以是一个不错的纪念品，这种小尺寸物件也很适合用手机拍照。“火柴盒日记”记录了纯白背景下纽约餐厅风格各异的火柴盒设计。</p><p><b><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/coffeecupsoftheworld/\" rel=\"nofollow\">3. Coffee Cups of the World (@coffeecupsoftheworld)</a></b></p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160929013456U0bxLoc47KdqemGB.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.991935\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160929013536AkuCaz2PfTlDHxyJ.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.003273\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><span style=\"text-align: justify;\"></span><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160929013652ivOdkwfn0TajcgLB.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.990307\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure></div><p><span style=\"text-align: justify;\">这里你不会找到星巴克的杯子。Coffee Cups of the World 记录了世界各地独立咖啡店的一流咖啡纸设计。例如旧金山一家名为 Dandelion Chocolates 的巧克力店，咖啡杯一侧长了一个“袋鼠口袋”，刚好可以放下一块热烘烘的曲奇。</span></p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><span style=\"text-align: justify;\"></span><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160929014645PdN8agKC0fvrEHRy.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.990588\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure></div><p class=\"\"><span style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br></span></p><p><b><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/dailyoverview/\" rel=\"nofollow\">4. Daily Overview (@dailyoverview)</a></b></p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160929014448Q7EwFlHhySAKbqjx.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.233379\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160929014516rpJWTNdmku78QZzx.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.249661\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160929014552ZDE3RsdrTUN96AGf.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.118824\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure></div><p>每个在飞机上望向窗外的人都会有类似的感受——俯瞰的地球太美了。这个账户就像是一个你随时随地可以向外看的窗户，在这里你可以看到沙特阿拉伯被灌溉之后的农田，加那利群岛沙滩上热烈的太阳伞，或者哥本哈根蜿蜒的自行车道。</p><p><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/breezeblockhead/\" rel=\"nofollow\"><b>5. Sam Marshall (@breezeblockhead)</b></a></p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160929014102WgtXcoqM5fvahswd.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.998824\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><span style=\"text-align: justify;\"></span><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160929014413CHyumE10A74DpUl6.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.997647\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><span style=\"text-align: justify;\"></span><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160929014426FWGBvx3JPhYHujVd.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.998824\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure></div><p><span style=\"text-align: justify;\">“breezeblock”，指通常中间有两个洞的长方形水泥砖，在北美被叫做“cinderblocks”。线上词典 </span><a href=\"http://www.urbandictionary.com/define.php?term=breezeblock\" style=\"text-align: justify; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\" rel=\"nofollow\">Urban Dictionary </a><span style=\"text-align: justify;\">对它们的描述是“便宜的建筑可以完全用它们建成，不过看起来很第三世界。”澳大利亚建筑师 Sam Marshall 是一个 breezeblock 的狂热分子，他拍摄了各种形状、堆叠方式、在阳光下投射奇妙阴影的 breezeblock，这种廉价的材质被他拍出了艺术品的美感。</span></p><p><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/theacademynewyork/\" rel=\"nofollow\"><b>6. The Academy (@theacademynewyork)</b></a></p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><span style=\"text-align: justify;\"></span><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160929011632BE8Q4a6DIhMy2Hlg.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.670017\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><span style=\"text-align: justify;\"></span><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160929011641VeX5A8vIZBrzFcn1.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.243750\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><span style=\"text-align: justify;\"></span><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160929011654yCTYqgFbJnGisaQN.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.965058\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure></div><p><span style=\"text-align: justify;\">教堂的彩色玻璃、示威者举起的牌子、晾晒的床单，这三个东西有什么共同点？在纽约服装品牌 The Academy 的账户里，三个东西都是彩色条纹的产物。账户不断放出三个一组的主题照片，关注者像解一个谜——找出三张照片的共同主题，而这个主题可以是任何东西。</span></p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><span style=\"text-align: justify;\"></span><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160929011706zMYEVfv71DPLgsl4.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.000000\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><b></b><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160929011715oFWag2jfITJ3ySBc.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.996672\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><b></b><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160929011723LPnQ6vRXUtCw3lsx.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.245833\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure></div><p><b><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/inter_disciplinary/\" rel=\"nofollow\">7. Hayley Eichenbaum (@inter_disciplinary)</a></b></p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160929012038iBV1PzD3jJQK0Exv.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.395683\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160929011951Wl142SCAUYn0rjQt.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.803787\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160929012001FqKW1UbxVgfEdnAO.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.226695\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160929012146x2KyzCpvQ47r8Wjg.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.381862\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure></div><p>洛杉矶摄影师<a href=\"http://www.hayley-eichenbaum.com\" rel=\"nofollow\"> Hayley Eichenbaum</a> 记录美国西部的各种酒店。Eichenbaum 没有受过正规的摄影训练，大部分照片是用一台尼康 D7100 和苹果手机拍下。<a href=\"https://www.wired.com/2016/03/sun-drenched-photos-will-make-long-great-american-west/\" rel=\"nofollow\">她从 2013 年开通了 Instagram 账号，第二年她花了一个月时间沿着美国 66 号国道漫游美国西部，拍了 15000 张照片</a>，觉得西部一切都美妙极了。</p><p><b><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/labeltime/\" rel=\"nofollow\">8. LABELS! (@labeltime)</a></b></p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160929015150fjPqmInLsQdCV7gc.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.001645\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160929015850tKx3alJChiyz8UXm.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.998824\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160929015925wvGdcIafXSjVnCUY.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.002353\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure></div><p><span style=\"text-align: justify;\">衣服上的商标标签，人人都有！不过我们大概也都有过被标签弄痒了脖子的经历，现在商家倾向于把衣服尺寸和成分直接印在布料上，这些小片的标签现在出现得越来越少，一些有年代的标签有了文物的意思。LABELS! 把设计有趣新鲜的标签们记录了下来。</span></p><p><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/berlin_memories/\" rel=\"nofollow\"><b>9. Berlin Memories (@berlin_memories)</b></a></p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201609290156273f578HePcgELrd6Y.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.718287\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160929015638BabTED9F03mx6uKG.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.798701\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160929015656Uloe8LTMB7bKhAfa.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.776886\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201609290157053uT80QzsrVpHRmjt.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.761675\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure></div><p>柏林有超过 170 个地铁站，这个账号的主人 Claudio Galamini 把每一个地铁站都拍了下来。和纽约、伦敦等大城市地铁系统类似，柏林地铁站的设计同样花样繁多。</p><p><b><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/handdryers/\" rel=\"nofollow\">10. Hand Dryers (@handdryers)</a></b></p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201609290155135igmD31ULe2hFGjf.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.011457\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160929015534Nbn6M8kByzqW3xEh.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.772213\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160929015604LmCwcRHOf5rZQ9ta.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.995138\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure></div><p>在各个地方随处可见的烘手机。这里的烘手机经常不那么光洁如新，而是很可能被乱涂乱画、贴上贴纸，还可能顶着一个醉汉留下的啤酒瓶。在其中一张照片里，甚至烘手机本身已经不在了——“一个倒下的战士”，作者在描述中写道。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160929015614FjWSbZ3zVDvKia1M.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.980769\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure></div><p class=\"\">图片来自：Instagram，<a href=\"https://www.wired.com/2016/09/10-hyper-specific-instagram-accounts-thrill-inner-design-nerd/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Wired</a></p>"}